    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="bb-muted">Draft — last updated July 2026.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>A pseudonymous handle and your email address. No real-name fields exist.</li>
        <li>Your <strong>birth year only</strong> — never your full date of birth. The full date
            is used once, transiently, to confirm you are 21+, and is discarded.</li>
        <li>Your ratings, tasting notes, check-ins, and contributions to the shared catalog.</li>
        <li>First-party product events (for example "signup" or "rating") stored in our own
            database. <strong>No third-party analytics or trackers, ever.</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we never do</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Sell, export, or log your individual behavioral data to anyone. Anything shared
            externally is aggregate only.</li>
        <li>Keep IP addresses beyond transient abuse control.</li>
        <li>Collect phone numbers, precise home location, or real names.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your controls</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Export:</strong> download everything we hold about you as JSON from your
            profile, any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete:</strong> from your profile, choose full deletion or anonymization
            (public contributions stay under an anonymous handle). Personal data is purged either
            way, after a short change-your-mind window.</li>
        <li>Per-rating privacy toggle, hide-me-from-matches, and one-click digest unsubscribe.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where data lives</h2>
    <p>
        On servers we operate in the EU (Hetzner), fronted by Cloudflare. Nightly encrypted
        backups are kept for 30 days, then deleted.
        @* [FLAG] EU hosting + US users — counsel to confirm no additional notice needed. *@
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Privacy questions or requests: see <a href="/legal/contact">Contact &amp; reporting</a>.</p>
</article>
